cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with person re-identification using RGB-infrared images, which is a computer vision task related to image processing and analysis. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel multi-spectrum image generation method and a one-stream neural network, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also addresses the challenge of modality discrepancy, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with infrared images, which is a subfield of image processing and analysis, making cs.IR (Image and Video Processing) a possible category as well.
